3E. EASY CODING (from all_in_one_question_3 — Part 4)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  [C][ ] (E) Without any if/else/ternary, print 1 if a > b, -1 if a < b, 0 if equal.
             Hint: (a > b) - (a < b)
             Asked at: Samsung, Dolat Capital

  [C][ ] (E) Check if two floats are equal up to 6 decimal places.
             Use: fabs(a - b) < 1e-6
             Asked at: Zoho, Dolat Capital

  [C][ ] (E) Without any loop, find the absolute value of an integer without abs().
             Use: (x < 0) ? -x : x  OR  (x ^ (x >> 31)) - (x >> 31)
             Asked at: Samsung, Sasken

  [C][ ] (E) Read two integers a and b. Print their average WITHOUT overflow.
             Hint: a/2 + b/2 + (a%2 + b%2)/2
             Asked at: Amazon, Google

  [C][ ] (E) Given 3 bits x, y, z, compute the majority bit (1 if at least 2 are 1).
             Hint: (x & y) | (y & z) | (x & z)
             Asked at: Dolat Capital, competitive programming

